{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "To combine the feature maps extracted by both the encoders, we design a channel attention fusion (CAF) module that incorporates a squeeze-and-excitation (SE) block [20] for channel attention.",
    "The SE block selectively emphasizes the informative features from both encoders, facilitating the integration of high-level and local information.",
    "The attention mechanism within the CAF module enables effective feature combinations.",
    "The combined features using the CAF module constitute the input to the decoder, where the mask image is reconstructed using skip connections from the efficient-NetV2 encoder.",
    "In addition to the power of the ViTs encoder, we opted to use efficientNetV2 [19] instead of a CNN encoder, because efficientNetV2 uses a technique called compound scaling to increase the depth, width, and resolution of the network in a balanced manner."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To combine the feature maps extracted by both the encoders, we design a channel attention fusion (CAF) module that incorporates a squeeze-and-excitation (SE) block [20] for channel attention.",
